\noindent \textbf{MV-GRPO Objective}.
Instead of collapsing the multi-view information into a single scalar reward, we propose to fully leverage the augmented condition space by treating each view in $\mathcal{V}_K$ as a valid optimization trajectory. This formulation allows the policy to learn robust alignment features that satisfy both the original instruction and the discriminative augmented descriptors.

Formally, for any condition $\mathbf{c}' \in \mathcal{V}_K$, we first compute the view-specific advantage $A_i(\mathbf{c}')$ for the $i$-th sample:
\begin{equation}
    A_i(\mathbf{c}') = \frac{R(\mathbf{x}_0^i, \mathbf{c}') - \text{mean}(\{R(\mathbf{x}_0^j, \mathbf{c}')\}_{j=1}^G)}{\text{std}(\{R(\mathbf{x}_0^j, \mathbf{c}')\}_{j=1}^G)}.
\end{equation}
The final MV-GRPO objective is constructed by aggregating the policy gradient losses across the anchor view $\mathbf{c}$ and the $K$ selected augmented views $\{\mathbf{c}_{(k)}\}_{k=1}^K$. Following the structure of PPO, the total objective is defined as:

\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
    \mathcal{J}_{\text{MV}}(\theta) = \mathbb{E}_{\{\mathbf{x}^i\} \sim \pi_{\theta_{\text{old}}}(\cdot|\mathbf{c})} \Bigg[ 
    & \underbrace{ \frac{1}{G} \sum_{i=1}^G \mathcal{L}_{\text{PPO}}(\mathbf{x}^i, \mathbf{c}, A_i(\mathbf{c})) }_{\text{Objective for Anchor View}} \\
    + \lambda & \underbrace{ \frac{1}{K} \sum_{k=1}^K \frac{1}{G} \sum_{i=1}^G \mathcal{L}_{\text{PPO}}(\mathbf{x}^i, \mathbf{c}_{(k)}, A_i(\mathbf{c}_{(k)})) }_{\text{Objective for Augmented Views}} 
    \Bigg] - \beta D_{\text{KL}}(\pi_\theta \| \pi_{\text{ref}}),
\end{aligned}
\label{eq:mv_objective}
\end{equation}
where $\lambda$ is a weighting coefficient balancing the primary task and auxiliary supervision. The per-sample PPO loss term $\mathcal{L}_{\text{PPO}}$ is given by:
\begin{equation}
    \mathcal{L}_{\text{PPO}}(\mathbf{x}, \mathbf{c}', A) = \frac{1}{T} \sum_{t=0}^{T-1} \min \left( \rho_t(\mathbf{c}') A, \text{clip}(\rho_t(\mathbf{c}'), 1-\varepsilon, 1+\varepsilon) A \right),
\end{equation}
with the importance sampling ratio conditioned on the specific view $\mathbf{c}'$:
\begin{equation}
    \rho_t(\mathbf{c}') = \frac{\pi_\theta(\mathbf{x}_{t-1} | \mathbf{x}_t, \mathbf{c}')}{\pi_{\theta_{\text{old}}}(\mathbf{x}_{t-1} | \mathbf{x}_t, \mathbf{c}')}.
\end{equation}
By optimizing this joint objective, MV-GRPO ensures that the generated policy is not only aligned with the initial user prompt but also consistent with the intrinsic visual semantics captured by the augmented views.
